TY  - JOUR
AU  - Norets, A.
AU  - Tang, X.
T1  - Semiparametric Inference in Dynamic Binary Choice Models
PY  - 2014
Y1  - 2014/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdt050
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 81
IS  - 3
SP  - 1229
EP  - 1262
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We introduce an approach for semiparametric inference in dynamic binary choice models that does not impose distributional assumptions on the state variables unobserved by the econometrician. The proposed framework combines Bayesian inference with partial identification results. The method is applicable to models with finite space of observed states. We demonstrate the method on Rust's model of bus engine replacement. The estimation experiments show that the parametric assumptions about the distribution of the unobserved states can have a considerable effect on the estimates of per-period payoffs. At the same time, the effect of these assumptions on counterfactual conditional choice probabilities can be small for most of the observed states.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdt050
ER  - 



